I try to keep my species culture-coding as open as I can and only do it for those that really count or are really good at representing a specific culture. If your headcanon is 'Earth but with anthro' like mine is, it would come natural.
Panda Bears are a good example of an animal that represents a country (China) to the point of being universally associated.
Native American tribes used to literally live alongside the Bison, migrating with their herds because they were so important to them.

>>61059141
It's still fun to mess around with though when it comes to worldbuilding. It's not meant to be race politics or anything like that, more so culture and how Anthro cultures would develop alongside Human culture. We've been associating animals with people for a long long time, and anthro equivalents are an extension of that.

You are right, however, that animals can't really be tied to one place as easily as Human cultures, but with Anthro species that'd be different. culture coding therefore works best with animals like the Giant Panda or the Iberian Lynx, and not Foxes, Deer or Wolves.
